    {
        " changes, which are less objectionable than the equivalent hue changes of NTSC. A minor drawback is that the vertical colour resolution is poorer than the NTSC systems, but since the human eye also has a colour resolution that is much lower than its brightness resolution, this effect is not visible. In any case, NTSC, PAL, and SECAM all have chrominance bandwidth reduced greatly compared to the luminance signal.                      The 4.43361875  MHz frequency of the colour carrier is a result of 283.75 colour clock cycles per line plus a 25  Hz offset to avoid interferences. Since the line frequency is 15625  Hz , the colour ": null
